<TITLE> 3 children, 2 women perish in Lalbagh fire </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 4 (bdnews24.com)  Five people, including three children, died in a fire at the old city's Lalbagh area at on Thursday, said firefighters. The fire originated from an Islambagh foam factory at around 12:30 pm that spread to surrounding buildings. The dead were identified as Amena, 55, her six-month old grandson Sazzad, Sathia Begum, 35, her one year old son Emon and Sharmin, 4, all residents of an adjacent building. All five were died while taking shelter in a downstairs escaping from the second floor. Fire brigade deputy director Mizanur Rahman told bdnews24.com that they had recovered one body from the spot. "Five people were recovered unconscious." bdnews24.com Dhaka Medical College Hospital correspondent said that the duty doctor declared Sazad, Sathia Begum, Emon and Sharmin dead on arrival. Two fire fighters were also injured during the rescue operation, he said. The blaze was brought under control e at around 3 pm. The fire gutted some 15 or 20 buildings in the area, most of them plastic factories. Losses were estimated at Tk 20 lakh. bdnews
